Notey is a blog search and discovery platform founded in 2015 that helps users discover non-mainstream content and blogs. The platform ranks and features both bloggers and independent publishers on various topics including technology, weddings, sneakers and more than 500,000 others. Users can upvote articles they like, save them in notebooks and see what the community is reading.
In April 2015, Business Insider named Notey “one of the fastest growing startups in the world still flying under the radar”.
The company is based in Hong Kong and San Francisco. Its investors include Hugo Barra, Ryan Holmes, Shakil Khan and Steve Kirsch.
